item.title: Grand Circle Island and Haleiwa 9 Hour Tour
item.description: Perfect for first-time visitors, or those with limited time, this full-day tour takes you all around Oahu, making sure that you don't miss a thing. You'll explore top attractions including Diamond Head, Hanauma Bay, Halona Blowhole, the Byodo-In Temple and the surfing beaches of the North Shore. You'll also have enough time to discover the charming town of Haleiwa.

image.alt: Grand Circle Island and Haleiwa 9 Hour Tour

item.title: Salute to Pearl Harbor Including USS Arizona
item.description: While visiting Honolulu, take a half-day tour of Pearl Harbor that details the history of World War II in Hawaii. Visit the World War II Valor in the Pacific National Monument and Battleship Row with a guide who shares informative commentary about Oahu during the war in the Pacific.

image.alt: Salute to Pearl Harbor Including USS Arizona

item.title: Oahu Circle Island: Snorkel with Turtles & Explore in Small Group
item.description: Explore Oahu on this full-day minibus tour with a small group and a local guide. With your small group of 24-28 people or fewer, make plenty of stops at the island's highlights, including snorkeling with green sea turtles on the North Shore. See the Dole Plantation, the Halona Blowhole, Diamond Head, and Makapu’u Beach during this day-long outing. Round-trip transportation from Waikiki hotels is included.

image.alt: Oahu Circle Island: Snorkel with Turtles & Explore in Small Group

item.title: Majestic Circle Island Tour with Lunch
item.description: If you have just one day to explore Oahu, the Circle Island Drive is a must—taking in all the island’s highlights in just one day. This full-day tour from Honolulu visits Nu’uanu Pali, Byodo-In Temple, Tropical Farms Macadamia Nut Farm, the Dole Plantation, and Waimea Valley. Hotel pickup and drop-off is included.

image.alt: Majestic Circle Island Tour with Lunch

item.title: Oahu's Ultimate Tour: Dole, Turtle Snorkel, & Byodo Temple
item.description: If you have only limited time to explore Oahu, make the most of it with this full-day circle island tour. Not a minute is wasted on this action-packed tour that takes you to Byodo-In Temple, the Dole Plantation, secret beaches, island hotspots and more. You'll also have the chance to snorkel in turtle-filled water on the North Shore.

image.alt: Oahu's Ultimate Tour: Dole, Turtle Snorkel, & Byodo Temple

item.title: Deluxe Pearl Harbor, USS Arizona Memorial & Honolulu City Tour
item.description: Experience the highlights of downtown Honolulu and the USS Arizona Memorial in absolute comfort on this half-day sightseeing tour by coach. Aboard air-conditioned transport, pass attractions including the Iolani Palace, King Kamehameha statue, and the Punchbowl National Cemetery, while listening to informative commentary from your driver-guide. Learn Pearl Harbor history at the USS Arizona Memorial Visitor Center. Upgrade to include entry to the USS Missouri battleship and/or the Pearl Harbor Aviation Museum.

image.alt: Deluxe Pearl Harbor, USS Arizona Memorial & Honolulu City Tour

item.title: Grand Tour Around Island 16 Locations plus Snorkeling
item.description: With just one day, you can see 16 of Oahu’s greatest sights and still have time for snorkeling—if you hop on this tour. Across one whirlwind day, you’ll witness Diamond Head State Monument, the Halona Blowhole, the Dole Plantation, and so much more. You’ll capture fantastic photos, learn all about the island’s history, and go snorkeling, topping off the day surrounded by Oahu’s colorful marine life.

image.alt: Grand Tour Around Island 16 Locations plus Snorkeling

item.title: Pearl Harbor Remembered Tour
item.description:
Sightseeing in Hawaiʻi isn’t complete without a visit to the two symbolic “bookends” of the Pacific War, the USS Arizona whose bombing was the catalyst that propelled the US into WWII, and the USS Missouri on whose decks the Japanese formally surrendered. Pearl Harbor Remembered Tour is led by a guide whose knowledge of and appreciation for these historic sites makes this “memorial” tour an experience to remember.
Stops and drive-by sites on the Pearl Harbor Remembered may include: •Pearl Harbor Visitor Center – Experience world-class museums, waterfront exhibits, the bookstore and more. • USS Arizona Memorial-View a 23-minute documentary about December 7, 1941, then take a shuttle boat ride to board the USS Arizona Memorial. Shuttle boat ride tickets to the USS Arizona Memorial may be canceled or modified due to mechanical issues, high winds, or other safety concerns. Reservations are non-refundable. • Ford Island and the USS Missouri Battleship • Historic Downtown Honolulu

image.alt: Pearl Harbor Remembered Tour

item.title: Pearl Harbor USS Arizona Memorial
item.description: The Pearl Harbor National Monument is a must-visit when coming to Oahu. Guarantee your entry, including boat tickets to the USS Arizona, with this tour. Take a tour of the visitor's center, where you watch a short film and explore exhibits that recount the infamous morning of December 7, 1941.

image.alt: Pearl Harbor USS Arizona Memorial

item.title: Tour of North Shore & Waimea Waterfall
item.description: This tour allows you to see the sights of the North Shore of Oahu, including Hanauma Bay. During this full-day tour, ride in a mini-bus to the Dole Plantation, Turtle Town, the Banzai Pipeline, and either Waimea Bay to swim or take the botanical garden waterfall hike or go hiking in Waimea Valley. Pickup and drop-off at Waikiki hotels are included.

image.alt: Tour of North Shore & Waimea Waterfall

item.title: Pearl Harbor City Tour
item.description: Come along on this 5 hour tour of historical sites, including the Historic Downtown Honolulu, Pearl Harbor National Memorial and the USS Arizona Memorial.

image.alt: Pearl Harbor City Tour

item.title: All Inclusive Ultimate Circle Island Tour, Waimea Falls & Lunch
item.description: Leave all the logistics of exploring Oahu up to this Circle Island all-inclusive day tour that lets you run on a Hawaiian time. Along with round-trip transport from Honolulu, lunch, and all entry fees included, you also take home a 152-page Oahu nature book. Plus, a guide navigates the island so you can see main highlights such as Diamond Head, Halona Blowhole, Valley of the Temples, Mokoli'i Island, and more.

image.alt: All Inclusive Ultimate Circle Island Tour, Waimea Falls & Lunch

item.title: Waikiki Catamaran Adventure: Snorkel with Sea Turtles
item.description: Snorkel with green sea turtles in Oahu's Turtle Canyon on this tour departing from Waikiki. Board a power catamaran and sail along the shore of Oahu towards the island's best place to spot the resident turtles. Turtle sightings are guaranteed; if a turtle is not sighted, you will be given a free second cruise. After snorkeling, enjoy lunch and two alcoholic drinks and unlimited soft drinks provided while you keep your eyes peeled for passing marine life like dolphins and migrating whales.

image.alt: Waikiki Catamaran Adventure: Snorkel with Sea Turtles

item.title: Oahu Deluxe Grand Circle Island Tour
item.description: Circle the Island of Oahu by coach, enjoying ocean views, rugged mountains, and fascinating history during this full-day tour. Check out Diamond Head, Nu’uanu Pali lookout, the Halona Blowhole, Waimea Valley and Oahu’s beautiful North Shore. Soak up Hawaiian history and culture with a stop at the Dole Plantation and the serene, Japanese-style Byodo-In Temple. This Oahu circle island tour also includes entrance fees at the temple and round-trip hotel transport.

image.alt: Oahu Deluxe Grand Circle Island Tour

item.title: The Magical Mystery Show! at Hilton Waikiki Beach Hotel
item.description: Step into a world of enchantment—and get a memorable night out—with this magical mystery show. Reviving the allure of Victorian-era parlors, where social elites indulged in fine dining and captivating arts, you’ll sit just steps away from your Parlor Magician, barely believing your eyes. A mesmerizing performance in an elegant settings, maybe magic and miracles do exist.

image.alt: The Magical Mystery Show! at Hilton Waikiki Beach Hotel

item.title: Oahus Cozy 14 Passenger Circle Island Tour + Food Discount Card
item.description: This small-group circle-island tour of Oahu is ideal for those who want to see a lot in a short time. In a cozy vehicle with no more than 14 passengers, you'll see such landmarks as Diamond Head, the Halona Blowhole, Byodo-In Temple and the historic Haleiwa Town. You'll also visit the famed Dole Plantation where you'll get a whole delicious Dole pineapple.

image.alt: Oahus Cozy 14 Passenger Circle Island Tour + Food Discount Card

item.title: Pearl Harbor USS Arizona Memorial & Battleship Missouri
item.description: Learn about World War II history on this guided group tour to Pearl Harbor, which includes round-trip transfers from Waikiki hotels. Visit the Pearl Harbor Visitor's Center and get to explore inside the USS Battleship Missouri and the USS Arizona Memorial Boat, where you learn about the war and get an idea of what life at sea was like during the war.

image.alt: Pearl Harbor USS Arizona Memorial & Battleship Missouri

item.title: Oahu Grand Circle Island Experience from Waikiki
item.description: Spend a day exploring the highlights of Oahu without the hassle of driving on this full-day island tour. Join a small group to circumnavigate the island stopping at key landmarks including Diamond Head, Makapu’u Point, and the Dole Plantation. While you drive, take in the beautiful scenery of white sand beaches, lush valleys, sacred Hawaiian grounds, and the waves of the Pacific Ocean.

image.alt: Oahu Grand Circle Island Experience from Waikiki

item.title: Pearl Harbor: USS Arizona Memorial & USS Missouri Battleship Tour from Waikiki
item.description: This Pearl Harbor tour departs from Waikiki and includes visits to both the USS Arizona Memorial (tickets cannot be guaranteed) and the USS Missouri battleship. Beforehand, you'll have the chance to learn about the Japanese attack at the Pearl Harbor Visitor Center, including its powerful documentary. The ride back to Waikiki takes you past Punchbowl (the National Memorial Cemetery of the Pacific) and the King Kamehameha statue.

image.alt: Pearl Harbor: USS Arizona Memorial & USS Missouri Battleship Tour from Waikiki

item.title: Oahu Catamaran Cruise: Snorkeling, Wildlife and Hawaiian Meal
item.description: Sail on a catamaran down Oahu's western coast during this cruise from Ko Olina. Glide through the unspoiled waters on this side of the island in search of dolphins and whales, then dive in for a snorkeling experience in a hidden local spot rich with marine life. Enjoy a Hawaiian buffet, including alcoholic and non-alcoholic drinks, before heading back to shore. Choose from three daily departure times.

image.alt: Oahu Catamaran Cruise: Snorkeling, Wildlife and Hawaiian Meal

item.title: Waikiki Sunset Cocktail Cruise Including Drinks and Appetizers
item.description: View the Hawaiian sunset from the deck of a luxury catamaran during this all-inclusive cruise from Oahu. Take off from Honolulu, and glide along the coastline from Waikiki toward Diamond Head while enjoying the vibrant colors of the island sunset, an individualized light bento box of appetizers, two alcoholic drinks, and unlimited non-alcoholic drinks.

image.alt: Waikiki Sunset Cocktail Cruise Including Drinks and Appetizers

item.title: Diamond Head Crater
item.description: Experience Diamond Head Crater, one of Oahu’s most-loved hikes, on a self guided tour with a map, water, park entrance fees and round-trip transportation provided. The tour is fully customizable, so take your time or challenge yourself, and enjoy the stunning views from the 760-foot summit. Hotel departures are early in the morning to insure you avoid the big crowds later in the day. This tour is ideal for anyone looking for a bit of adventure and exercise and wanting to see one of Oahu’s most famous landmarks.

image.alt: Diamond Head Crater

item.title: Wild Dolphin Watching and Snorkel Safari Off West Coast of Oahu
item.description: Cruise along west Oahu’s pristine shoreline to see the spinner dolphins, humpback whales (seasonally), and other marine creatures that frequent the Waianae Coast. Your 32-foot USCG vessel is led by a lifeguard-certified crew of marine biologists and naturalists, maximizing your chances of spotting Hawaii’s underwater wildlife. Plus, with snorkeling gear included, you can choose to swim alongside tropical fish and sea turtles, too.

image.alt: Wild Dolphin Watching and Snorkel Safari Off West Coast of Oahu

item.title: Royal Crown of Oahu - 60 Min Helicopter Tour - Doors Off or On
item.description: Explore Hawaii’s island of Oahu by air on this helicopter tour. Fly above the island and many of its most well-known landmarks, such as Diamond Head, Sacred Falls, the Dole Plantation, and Pearl Harbor. On this ride, choose your departure time and whether or not you’d like the helicopter doors on or off.

image.alt: Royal Crown of Oahu - 60 Min Helicopter Tour - Doors Off or On
